Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.72,0:02:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, this just doesn't suit my style...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.64,0:02:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to just sit and wait like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.47,0:02:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We pick our spot, then wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the secret behind fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.77,0:02:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever consider that\Nmaybe this was the {\i1}wrong {\i0}spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.02,0:02:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bait has no right to complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you fishing for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Starship Pirates." A group\Nthat calls themselves pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.74,0:02:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.91,0:02:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A group of people that like to attack a ship\Nand rob anything and everything from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.45,0:02:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like to rob, rob, drunken slob!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, where the hell did Spike go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.09,0:02:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He left to overhaul his ship, and still hasn't--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.14,0:02:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Spike... Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.97,0:02:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing now,\Nwithout giving us a heads-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.29,0:03:10.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Doohan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strike three! Batter out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just let that one slide by...\Nand that's the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't they just send in a pinch-hitter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.68,0:03:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Eightwood is getting {\i1}old{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ya think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Doohan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.73,0:03:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man's kinda busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Miles, his assistant. Nice to meet ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, they were really great when\Nthey won the pennant 14 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They just kept hittin' the ball one after\Nanother, and turned losing games around!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:04:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when Randy, Blanket,\Nand Hills hit consecutive homers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.22,0:04:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wish you coulda seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And ya know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.89,0:04:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do people often say\Nyou're the silent type?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And people often say\Nyou talk too much, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.65,0:04:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The... {\i1}Swordfish{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The machine back there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the amazing mono-racer\Nthat the old man built, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an old machine.\NI don't want it, but it's a part of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear ya...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Us Blue Sox fans feel like\Nwe fell for some wicked broad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really! I can't remember how many times\NI've thought about giving up on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh. Jesus, not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.12,0:05:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo. Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miles, where's the checklist?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's out there! I put it on the ship's body!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been fixing that ancient thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The computer isn't compatible\Nwith the mono-system.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miles! Gimme the EV transmitter,\Nthe absorber for the main gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.89,0:05:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the three-eight pneumatic tube!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A three-eight?! I don't have\Nsomething that special!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Order one from Reggie. His place has them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. You really are some slave driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some hobby!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:05:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we catch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:06:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's close! Shit, I used bad bait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a good machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attacking blessed people like\Nthem and giving to the poor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.56,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is human equality. Don't you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, heh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what ya call social reform.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's only right for us,\Nthe poor, to take from them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.32,0:06:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cops?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.87,0:06:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bounty hunter...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Herman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be a good girl and come here...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.88,0:06:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Faye, above you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?! Is this a joke?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth! One more behind us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.69,0:07:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's {\i1}huge{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.44,0:07:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a tattered old ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Abnormality found in the mono-system.\NBooting the emergency pilot program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop this thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I know how!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's taken you\Non quite a few spins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The accelerator pump is all worn down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.28,0:08:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.28,0:08:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fuel injector\Ndoesn't have a silencer on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't need one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's noisy, and it trembles--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.33,0:08:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you put one in, then I can't\Nhear what it's telling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:08:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hurry up and connect the injector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, a three-eight\Nisn't popular anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.55,0:09:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you switch to the new five-zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.68,0:09:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you change the\Nnavigation to full-auto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then you can glide along\Nwithout manual steering--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to use a machine,\Nor do you want the machine to use you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.65,0:09:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't exactly--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.61,0:09:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, another assistant\Nis gonna leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.33,0:09:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you! The {\i1}Swordfish\N{\i0}wants to run away from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't heard that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep being reckless with her,\Nshe'll really throw you off someday!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I'm not\None for delicate controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got something you don't see often...\NA three-eight pneumatic tube!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you, Missing Man.\NWhere are you right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still with Doohan. How's Jet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems rather busy right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.92,0:10:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saying something about some bacteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bacteria?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A virus! We got a computer virus!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Starting with the mono-system,\Norbit calculator, flight path selector,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,engine regulator,\Ncommunications circuit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they're all shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it. Gimme a simple explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.36,0:10:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The computer broke and\Nwe're just drifting along!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I understood that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? It's the newest one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't seen one floating\Naround anywhere else, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mono-computer...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.45,0:10:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? 150K--No, 100K.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bargain, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it's sold {\i1}that {\i0}cheap,\Nyou lose money even on salvage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.46,0:10:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:10:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A truck? Any features?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A penguin...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...logo on...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the delivery truck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about the info?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They apparently were\Ndealing at the Orbit Drive-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Nobody would be suspicious\Nof a delivery truck wandering about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how are we going to counter the hacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get harpooned!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's {\i1}it{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They laughed this ship off as "tattered"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.47,0:11:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they made that mess\Nout of my {\i1}Hammerhead{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.05,0:11:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike {\i1}someone {\i0}I know,\NI always pay back what I owe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really not up for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.15,0:11:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have an invoice from Doohan here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.70,0:12:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they're {\i1}physically\N{\i0}sending the virus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they haven't developed a vaccine for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is where this secret\Nweapon of ours comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.75,0:12:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's just our normal communicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get infected by the virus,\Ncut off the entire mono-system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, all navigation and\Ncommunication will go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I said... I will navigate you with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because this is set to the frequency\Nfor an old communications satellite,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.52,0:12:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has nothing to do with the mono-system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, another run scored\Nagainst the Blue Sox!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's some secret weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosch throws his third pitch. It’s a ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.91,0:12:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s three balls, no strikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:12:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bosch is pitching wildly today.\NHe’s not getting it into the strike zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:13:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the catcher’s taking a while to--\Nah, looks like he’s finally made a signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a penguin, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. A purple penguin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, it might\Nbe a real courier service.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a matter of how to\Nfigure out if they are legit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.99,0:13:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We fire a shot, and the one\Nthat runs is the one we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time I agree\Nwith you on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.88,0:13:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You guys...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do\Nif they're both real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They both ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.35,0:13:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't consider that option...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trusting you with that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to pay them back for yesterday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We'll pay the parking fee!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike! Draw them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.35,0:14:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a mess if they\Nlet the virus go in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, let's see what ya got...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's after the arm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not taking us seriously! Ruth!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.71,0:15:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to go anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.18,0:15:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.76,0:15:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's holding up pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut off the mono-system!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot cut off his mono-system!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, George...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's in Earth's gravitational field...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man! Here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.47,0:15:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--This is pretty bad!\N--Align the D7. Ya did it before, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good! There's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Hurry up and\Ndo something about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit... Move! {\i1}Move{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.61,0:16:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Falling... We're falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calculating an interception course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, somehow keep control manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if everything was normal,\Nit'd be tough to get outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.38,0:16:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.51,0:16:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I just had it overhauled...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. Whatever happens, happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, above you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.03,0:17:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your tattered ship looks like a goddess!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, the virus...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.39,0:17:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to start over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.02,0:17:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! Old man, ya gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really gonna move\Nthis ancient piece of...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.07,0:17:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'd do this as a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.29,0:17:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just stand there!\NHurry up and get me some fuel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, can you hear me? I got a calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll take another 7 hours\Nfor us to rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.80,0:17:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you're joking, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're too close to Earth.\NThe orbital paths I can take are limited!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there a way for you\Nto just swing on by?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I plunge in at this angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both the {\i1}Bebop {\i0}and the {\i1}Swordfish\N{\i0}will burn to nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.41,0:18:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some booze hidden behind the fridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.38,0:18:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Feel free to drink some.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm outta gas. Nothing I can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about I go there and tow you back,\Nin exchange for that booze?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.80,0:18:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the conversation.\NGive me the {\i1}Swordfish{\i0}'s coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.23,0:18:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doohan?! How the hell do you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, I don't care how ya do it,\Nbut slow down using an air-brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slow down?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you slow down within Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.97,0:19:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the gravitational pull will\Naccelerate you instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.22,0:19:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which will give you enough speed to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you have to maintain\Nthe ship at a certain angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.89,0:19:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too far either way, and you'll be thrown\Nout to the other end of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.48,0:19:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I'm not\None for delicate controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't give you the {\i1}Swordfish {\i0}for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you start crashing, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maximum propulsion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to force\Nyourself to come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.60,0:20:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how Blue Sox fans love to party!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're flying...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.05,0:20:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're {\i1}really {\i0}flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lower the nose by 0.6 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in too deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spike, you'll burn to a crisp!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went in! It went in!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Doohan, you saved me.\N--Not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.48,0:21:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the heat-resistant\Ntiles have peeled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.95,0:21:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The temperature is rising...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.95,0:21:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The landing gear\Nisn't coming down either!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.66,0:21:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, and the #2 nozzle won't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.66,0:21:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?! Is that for real? What are we\Ngonna do? We can't land without them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.16,0:21:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Oh, well... Whatever happens, happens.\N--I'm only 18!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.96,0:22:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}knew {\i0}I shouldn't have come up here!\NI'm still too young to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.62,0:22:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Too much time has passed by...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.29,0:22:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...to lament that we were deeply in love.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.59,0:22:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wind keeps blowing, while my heart...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.22,0:22:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...cannot heal all the tears in it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.10,0:23:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone, cry for me with parched eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.70,0:23:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The real folk blues.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.16,0:23:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I only want to know what true sadness is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sitting in muddy water...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.30,0:23:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...isn't such a bad life...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.76,0:23:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...if it ends after the first time...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.82,0:24:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: "Pierrot Le Fou."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:22.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pierrot Le Fou"
